		   <table class="mform2"  border="0" cellpadding="1" cellspacing="0" width="100%">
		   <tr><td class="headerrow" colspan="2" class="mform2" valign="top">
		   <span class="sm">Posted @ Tue, Dec 5th 6:09 PM2000 </span><span id="notbold">| <span class=sm>IP: Logged</span> | <a class=sm href="/db/classes.html?class=1&mid=97601973416172&num=4&post=1&replyto=9760397295144"><img src=/shared/reply_to_thread_ico.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=11 width=17> Reply to this</a></a>    <a name=9760397295144></a></small></td></tr>
		   <tr><td valign="top" id="fs8" class="mform2" ><span id="notbold">By:</span> <a href="/db/poster.html?user=803"><span id=Scholar>GiddyGonzalus</span></a><b><span id=Scholar><br>Scholar</span></b><br><img src=/shared/user_star_ico.gif height=9 width=9><br>155 posts
		   <br><nobr><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Default [2.25]</nobr><br><br /><a href="/cgi-bin/pm.pl?action=addtolist&addname=GiddyGonzalus&type=Address" id="fs8"><img src="/shared/plus.gif" border="0" align="middle" height="9" width="9" alt="Add to address book"> Add to address book</a><br /><img src="/shared/transp.gif" width="135" border="0" height="1"></td><td valign="top" class="mform2" width="100%"><p>I tend to favour going after the toughest first as well (or caster first). It is likely that the toughest critter will be the one hitting most often and for the most damage. I don't like wasting time killing a guy that hits me once every 3 swings while his big brother is pounding my hiney back to Kaladim. It makes more sense to take less damage overall by taking out the toughest guys first.<br><br>Look at it this way. Regardless of which one you take out first, the total combat time will be the same. For example, say it will take your group 30 seconds to take out the little guy and 60 seconds to take out the tough guy. You can therefore have the little guy beat on you for 90 seconds, or the big guy beat on you for 90 seconds. When you look at it this way, the choice is pretty obvious, even to a Troll.<br><br>Take out the big'uns first, then go after the wee ones. They make better desserts anyways 8P</p><span class=sm>----------------------------</span><br>________<br><br>I've travelled this world and have seen many wondrous things. You are not one of them.</td></td></tr><tr><td colspan="2" class="mform2"><table border=0 cellspacing=0 cellpadding=0 width="100%"><tr><td id=fs8></td><td align=right id=fs8 >0 Replies</td></tr></table></td></tr></table><tr><td>
