		   <br><nobr><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Decent [3.00]</nobr><br><br /><a href="/cgi-bin/pm.pl?action=addtolist&addname=Anonymous&type=Address" id="fs8"><img src="/shared/plus.gif" border="0" align="middle" height="9" width="9" alt="Add to address book"> Add to address book</a><br /><img src="/shared/transp.gif" width="135" border="0" height="1"></td><td valign="top" class="mform" width="100%"><p>Here is the layout of priority mobs in battle.<br><br>First, Casters (they deal high damage in short amounts of time)<br><br>Second, The heavy hitting tanks (souch as a Dervish Thug at a Derv camp)<br><br>Third, Armed Mobs (swords, axes ect.) This is for the weaker mobs that have weapons. A armed heavy hitter (such as a Dervish Thug with a sword)would go up to the top of the list to #2 again.<br><br>Fourth, All remaing mobs going from highest con down.<br><br>Hope this helps you out.<br><br>Magamus<br>Dwarf Warrior</p></td></td></tr><tr><td colspan="2" class="mform"><table border=0 cellspacing=0 cellpadding=0 width="100%"><tr><td id=fs8></td><td align=right id=fs8 >0 Replies</td></tr></table></td></tr></table><tr><td>
