		   <tr><td valign="top" id="fs8" class="mform2" ><span id="notbold">By:</span> <span id=>Anonymous</span></a><b><span id=></span></b>
		   <br><nobr><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Default [2.00]</nobr><br><br /><a href="/cgi-bin/pm.pl?action=addtolist&addname=Anonymous&type=Address" id="fs8"><img src="/shared/plus.gif" border="0" align="middle" height="9" width="9" alt="Add to address book"> Add to address book</a><br /><img src="/shared/transp.gif" width="135" border="0" height="1"></td><td valign="top" class="mform2" width="100%"><p>Okay, I don't understand the question. Are you soloing the Mob or is it a group effort? If you are soloing a mob, well, it might not be a good idea. But if it is One blue and the rest green...take out the Blue first. But if it is a group effort, definitely take out the stronger guy first, then take out the casters, then the whimps. Usually in a mob, the caster is much more weaker than the stronger of the tanks. You want to take out the guy dealing the most damage first. Have the tanks in the group deal with the enemy tanks, and tell the magic classes to take out the enemy casters. Because enemy casters still usually concentrate on your tanks even though they are being attacked by magic. But the tanks have the HP to withstand it! :)</p></td></td></tr><tr><td colspan="2" class="mform2"><table border=0 cellspacing=0 cellpadding=0 width="100%"><tr><td id=fs8></td><td align=right id=fs8 >1 Replies</td></tr></table><table width="100%"><tr><td class=mhback>&nbsp;</td><td class=mhback >Thread Subject</a></td><td class=mhback>Started by</a></td><td class=mhback>Replies</a></td><td class=mhback>Last Post</a></td><td class=mhback>Rating</a></td></tr></table></td></tr></table><tr><td>
