		   <tr><td valign="top" id="fs8" class="mform" ><span id="notbold">By:</span> <a href="/db/poster.html?user=13317"><span id=>Tanzen</span></a><b><span id=></span></b><br>9 posts
		   <br><nobr><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Decent [3.00]</nobr><br><br /><a href="/cgi-bin/pm.pl?action=addtolist&addname=Tanzen&type=Address" id="fs8"><img src="/shared/plus.gif" border="0" align="middle" height="9" width="9" alt="Add to address book"> Add to address book</a><br /><img src="/shared/transp.gif" width="135" border="0" height="1"></td><td valign="top" class="mform" width="100%"><p>I am not the most experienced warrior around, but IMHO, this is my group's typical battle plan if we are in a multiple pull situation.&nbsp;&nbsp;Having access to casters with Harmony/Mes is a HUGE benefit so that the group can better manage a fight.<br><br>1)  Casting mobs must die -- especially healers<br>2)  Heavy hitting melee types<br>3)  Caster mobs that may still be alive<br>4)  Runners<br>5)  Anything else left<br><br>This is a very, very generic statement since each and every fight may have different problems and specific issues.  The fight order means absolutely nothing if a caster, particularly a healer, gets engaged in melee.  That requires a target switch, keeping the previous mob still attacking you, but taunting any and all mobs off your caster.  If your caster is engaged, they cannot heal you or nuke the daylights out of the enemy casters.<br><br>There will also be situations with specific types of mobs (very nasty special attacks, incredibly strong/fast hits, etc) that will affect the battle order.  Multiple pulls are something I try and avoid, particularly if we are hunting any mobs with yellow potential.  More than one yellow can often mean a corpse run for the unlucky caster who we couldn't disengage long enough to get a gate fired off to safety.  If reds are involved, tank's job is to keep the mobs engaged long enough to get the caster's clear.<br><br>In closing, communication is absolutely the MOST important grouping function.  Make sure each member is aware of their strengths and what they are being asked to do in this group at this time.  In the fight, talk about what you plan to do and how you want to do it.  Please feel free to respond to this.  I am not an expert and am just sharing what I know and have seen work for me and the groups I run with in EQ.<br><br>Be safe and Happy Hunting<br><br></p><span class=sm>----------------------------</span><br>Tanzen Whacksem<br>65th rank Barbarian Warrior (Overlord)<br>Protectors of Harmony<br>Saryn</td></td></tr><tr><td colspan="2" class="mform"><table border=0 cellspacing=0 cellpadding=0 width="100%"><tr><td id=fs8></td><td align=right id=fs8 >0 Replies</td></tr></table></td></tr></table><tr><td class=mhback align=right><span class=mh id=fs8><a class=mh href=/db/classes.html?class=1><img src=/shared/root_thread_ico.gif border=0 alt="Up" width=17 height=11> Thread Index</a> |  <a class=mh href=/db/classes.html?class=1&post=1><img src=/shared/new_thread_ico.gif border=0 alt="New" width=17 height=11> New Subject</a> | <a class=mh href=/db/classes.html?class=1&mid=97601973416172&num=4&post=1&mid=97601973416172><img src=/shared/reply_to_thread_ico.gif border=0 alt="Reply" width=17 height=11> Reply to Thread</a></span></td></tr><tr><td><table width="100%" border="0" cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0" class="mform"><tr><td id="fs8">4 Posts [ <a href="/fsearch.html?base=class1">Search Forums</a> ]</nobr></td></tr></table>&nbsp;</td></tr>
